			 <AUTHOR>Sevier, John</AUTHOR> 
			 <DATE VALUE="1797-02-17">February 17, 1797 </DATE> 
			 <EXTENT>1p</EXTENT> 
			 <NOTE TYPE="summary">This document is a letter written by Governor
				John Sevier to Captains Sparks and Wade, dated February 17, 1797. Sevier wrote
				this letter in regards to a conference the captains were preparing to hold with
				the settlers living within Indian lands. Sevier pleaded with Sparks and Wade to
				show compassion and tenderness towards those people, for they would soon be
				forced to relocate.</NOTE> 
			 <NOTE TYPE="Collection">Governor John Sevier Papers</NOTE> 
