  <TEXT> 
	 <BODY> 
		<DIV1 TYPE="letter"><PB N="[1]"> 
		  <OPENER> 
			 <ADDRESS> 
				<ADDRLINE> 
				  <NAME TYPE="place">Knoxville</NAME> 
				  <DATE VALUE="1797-02-17">17 February 1797</DATE></ADDRLINE> 
				<ADDRLINE>Captains 
				  <NAME TYPE="person">Sparks</NAME> &amp; 
				  <NAME TYPE="person">Wade</NAME></ADDRLINE> 
			 </ADDRESS></OPENER> 
		  <P>As you are now on the eve of <ORIG REG="setting">siting</ORIG> out
			 to hold A <ORIG REG="Conference">Conferance</ORIG> with the inhabitants settled
			 in what is called the <ORIG REG="Indian">indian</ORIG> lands,
			 <ADD PLACE="supralinear">I hope</ADD> permit me to Solicit your paternal,
			 benevolent, and favorable indulgences towards those unfortunate people, by
			 Granting <ADD PLACE="supralinear">unto</ADD> them all the time and suitable
			 opportunity <DEL TYPE="overstrike">that may be</DEL> adequate to a preparation
		  for their removal; and in every other instance <ORIG
		  REG="afford">affoard</ORIG> unto them such marks of your humanity and
		  tenderness As the <ORIG REG="duties">dutyes</ORIG> of your offices and the
		  nature of the Case will <DEL TYPE="overstrike">admit of</DEL>
		  <ADD PLACE="supralinear">permit you</ADD> in doing of which you will lay me
		  under <DEL TYPE="overstrike">high</DEL> <ADD PLACE="supralinear">very</ADD>
		  great and lasting obligations</P> 
		  <CLOSER> 
			 <SALUTE>I have the honor to be <LB> With much Esteem &amp; respect
				<LB> Your 
				<ABBR EXPAN="Most obedient servant">Mo. ob. Sevt.</ABBR> <LB>
				Signed</SALUTE> 
			 <SIGNED> 
				<NAME TYPE="person">John Sevier</NAME></SIGNED></CLOSER> 
		</DIV1> 
	 </BODY> 
